The epicentre of the quake was at a depth of 257 kilometres. The agency said most big quakes in South America occur at a depth of 70 kilometres or higher. WASHINGTON - An earthquake with a magnitude of 7.0 struck southeastern Peru on Friday, the US Geological Survey said. The epicentre of the quake was at a depth of 257 kilometres. The agency said most big quakes in South America occur at a depth of 70 kilometres or higher. The quake hit at 0850 GMT about 27 kilometres northeast of the town of Azangaro, near the border with Bolivia.